snippet: Yemeni officials and extremists said Nasser al Wuhayshi, the leader of Al Qaeda’s Yemen affiliate, was killed last week; American officials said they could not confirm the reports.
abstract: United States officials investigate reports that Nasser al-Wuhayshi, leader of Al Qaeda in the Arabian Peninsula, has been killed in Yemen in American drone strike.

byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Rukmini Callimachi from New York; David D. Kirkpatrick from Cairo; Suliman Ali Zway from Tripoli, Libya; Kareem Fahim from Baghdad; and Shuaib Almosawa from Sana, Yemen.

lead_paragraph: Yemeni officials and extremists said Nasser al Wuhayshi, the leader of Al Qaeda’s Yemen affiliate, was killed last week; American officials said they could not confirm the reports.

headline.main: No. 2 Qaeda Leader May Have Died in U.S. Airstrike in Yemen
headline.print_headline: Death of Qaeda Leader in Yemen Is Unconfirmed
